<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Kresal and Jeff Bean 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HALLOW VICTORY? Add Orange Unified Schools Supt. Robert L. French to those 
unhappy about Disneyland giving free entrance on Halloween -- a smashing 
success for the Anaheim amusement park, with more than 40,000 visitors. French 
wrote Disneyland of his displeasure. Elementary school absences in his district 
that day more than doubled, and the district lost $6,000 in state revenue, 
which is based on attendance. . . . Said French: "As an educator, I am offended 
by this action." Note: Halloween 1995 is on a Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 CHECK MATES: When chess organizer Eric Hicks recently got permission to start 
a chess club at Las Palmas Elementary in San Clemente, he predicted to students 
they'd love it more than milk caps. . . . "Now, they're starting to believe 
me," he said. The club is so successful that the game is spreading to other 
campuses of the Capistrano Unified School District. District trustees this week 
established a formal chess program, in cooperation with the U.S. Chess 
Federation. 
</P>
<P>
 BOTH SIDES NOW: Not only is the Fullerton-Rancho Santiago community college 
rivalry the oldest in the state, it's also the closest. . . . The teams have 
met 70 times and the series stands at 33-33-4. They meet tonight at 7 at the 
Cal State Fullerton campus with first place on the line in the Mission 
Conference Central Division. Each is 4-0 in the division. Rancho Santiago Coach 
Dave Ogas played for Fullerton when it won the 1965 national championship. . . 
. Said Ogas: "I'm telling our players, 'I was once the enemy.' You can't lie to 
the kids." 
</P>
<P>
 RUN WITH HART: Wyatt Hart, top vote-getter in the San Juan Capistrano City 
Council election, raised the most money, but it also didn't hurt that his name 
was already well known in South County. For five years, Hart served as media 
spokesman for Sheriff Brad Gates. . . . The retired sheriff's captain figured 
his name appeared in newspapers "a few thousand times" long before he entered 
the race, and added: "I'm sure it did help." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
