</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A kitten trapped within an apartment's bathroom wall for five weeks died as 
rescuers using high-tech equipment tried to save it, the rescuers said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Various experts had been called in to try and free the traumatized cat, which 
they located with thermal-imaging equipment often used to find people trapped 
in accidents or earthquakes. 
</P>
<P>
 A team of three men worked about 16 hours, an International Rescue Corps 
spokesman said, and after removing the bathtub the kitten was retrieved. 
</P>
<P>
