<TEXT>
<P>
 The NAACP has told young members they are not eligible to vote in upcoming 
branch elections, apparently to block a takeover attempt of one chapter by a 
supporter of fired Executive Director Benjamin F. Chavis Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 The NAACP board of directors changed election rules to require members age 17 
to 20 to join as adults in order to vote in branch elections.Before the change, 
youth members could vote as long as they were in good standing. 
</P>
