<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; LAWYER 
GROUP ALTERS NAME TO REFLECT CONSUMER BENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Trial Lawyers Assn. announced this week that it is changing 
its name to Consumer Attorneys Assn. of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman for the 2,900-member organization said the name change was 
prompted by survey research showing that more than three times as many people 
believe a "trial lawyer" represents accused criminals, rather than being 
someone who represents aggrieved consumers suing corporations or insurance 
companies. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have always been champions for consumer protection," said the group's 
president, Bruce Broillet. "With our new name, we will be able to communicate 
our message to the public." 
</P>
