<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASSAGE OF PROP. 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When George Wallace stood in the schoolhouse door in Alabama in 1963, we 
Californians were outraged at his racist attempt to deny education to black 
children. Now we pass a law so Pete Wilson can stand in the schoolhouse door 
and deny education to brown children. I guess that not only makes us racist but 
hypocritical ones as well. 
</P>
<P>
 MARK ALEXANDER 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
