<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montclair Prep 21, Ganesha 0 -- Darrell Dent threw two touchdown passes and 
returned a punt for another score to lead Montclair Prep past Ganesha (5-5) at 
Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties (7-1) scored in the second quarter when Dent returned the punt 84 
yards for a touchdown. Bobby Neuman ran for a two-point conversion that gave 
the Mounties an 8-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Dent completed four of eight passes for 81 yards and rushed for 75 yards in 
four carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting running back Akil Anderson (three carries, 42 yards) left the game 
after he suffered a concussion in the first quarter. JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
