<TEXT>
<P>
 St. John Bosco 17, Alemany 14 -- Richard Williams drilled a 29-yard field goal 
with 1:43 remaining to give St. John Bosco the victory and keep the Braves' 
playoff hopes alive. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany (1-7-2, 0-5) tried a last-ditch comeback, but St. John Bosco 
linebacker Vincent Vigil sacked Alemany quarterback Danny Arguella at the 
Braves 27-yard line on the final play of the game. 
</P>
<P>
 St. John Bosco (5-5, 2-3) jumped out to a 14-0 lead in the first quarter on a 
25-yard touchdown run by Ryan Williams and Chad Carpenter's 25-yard 
interception return. But the Indians stormed back in the second quarter aided 
by two St. John Bosco fumbles. 
</P>
