YOUTH WILL BE SERVING FOR MASTER'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Master's College will start four sophomores and two juniors tonight 
against Southern California College in a National Assn. of Intercollegiate 
Athletics Far West regional volleyball match. 
</P>
<P>
 But that won't stop Mustang women's volleyball Coach Dean Cronk from counting 
on his team's experience. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs (27-12), seeded fourth, have played more matches this season than 
any team in the regional. Southern California College (17-10), which defeated 
the Mustangs earlier, is seeded fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's nothing like having experience," Conk said. "A lot of our early 
matches were in tournaments but it was something we needed. I hope to draw off 
that tonight." 
</P>
<P>
 Master's sophomore Wendy Jones has 459 kills and Heidi Elliott has a .364 
hitting percentage. BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
