<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAL LUTHERAN EXPERIENCES FIRST NCAA PLAYOFF VICTORY; VOLLEYBALL: YOUNG REGALS 
DEFEAT OCCIDENTAL IN FIVE GAMES IN WEST REGIONAL AT SAN DIEGO. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE KLEIMAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If the players on the Cal Lutheran women's volleyball team were nervous, it 
was understandable. 
</P>
<P>
 They were playing in an NCAA Division III West Regional for the first time and 
there isn't a senior on the team. 
</P>
<P>
 However, the Regals overcame early jitters to defeat Occidental, 5-15, 15-9, 
14-16, 15-9, 15-9, in a first-round match Friday night at UC San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran (20-8) plays tonight against the the winner of Friday's late 
match between second-ranked UC San Diego and Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
 As the score reflects, things didn't start well for the Regals. 
</P>
<P>
 "The nerves were there," Cal Lutheran Coach James Park said. "Oxy had been in 
the tournament (the past three years) and there was a difference." 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 4-0, in the second game, the Regals finally began to click. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior captain Darcy White epitomized the team's turnaround. 
</P>
<P>
 White, who had no kills in the first game, had eight in the fourth game and 
five in the fifth, including match point. She finished with a team high 20.  
</P>
<P>
 Freshman setter Liz Martinez had 42 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 During Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference play, the 
Regals split two matches with the Tigers (20-6), both of which also lasted five 
games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
