<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTMONT, MASTER'S PLAY IT AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Master's College and Westmont have been in this situation before.For the 
fifth time in six seasons, the teams will meet in the final of the National 
Assn. of Intercollegiate Athletics Far West Regional soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner of today's 1:30 p.m. match at Westmont advances to the NAIA 
Division I national finals at Mobile, Ala., later this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Westmont is ranked third and Master's 17th in the NAIA poll. Earlier this 
season, Westmont defeated Master's, 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's has played only twice since Oct. 22. The Mustangs defeated 
Christian Heritage, 6-0, to gain a berth the regional final, and played a 
scoreless tie with Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
