<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; RUN WILL RAISE FUNDS FOR SCHOOL FOUNDATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A five-kilometer run and a two-kilometer walk Sunday will raise money for 
projects of the Tustin Public Schools Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubbed "Dinosaur Dash 4," the event will begin and end in the Tustin Market 
Place at El Camino Real and Jamboree Road. 
</P>
<P>
 The 5-K run will begin at 8 a.m. and the 2-K walk will follow at 9:30 a.m. 
Race-day registration will start at 6:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The entry fee for adults is $20. The fee for children 11 or younger is $15. 
Participants will receive a T-shirt and a Dinosaur Dash milk cap. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Jennings, executive director of the Tustin Public Schools Foundation, 
said money raised from the event will be donated to Tustin schools to help 
enrich math, science, language, arts, reading, physical fitness and other 
school programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, the event raised more than $22,000 and attracted nearly 5,000 
participants, Jennings said. 
</P>
<P>
 The race features a wheelchair division, a dinosaur costume category and 
running teams from the police and fire departments, the military and clubs. The 
entry fee for five-member teams is $75. 
</P>
<P>
 Prizes will be awarded to the top finishers in 16 age divisions of the 5-K 
race. All finishers in the 2-K walk will receive a prize. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 832-6299. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
