<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FULLERTON; ELECTION SIGNS WANTED -- IN SPECIAL DUMPSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The election is over and firefighters say there is no reason for campaign 
signs to be up. 
</P>
<P>
 They want candidates to know a special trash bin just for campaign placards is 
waiting for their arrival behind the Commonwealth fire station. 
</P>
<P>
 "The city's cluttered with signs," Capt. Al Meacham said. "We want to make 
sure the signs come down before they become an eyesore. The signs serve a 
purpose before the election, but afterward we want to help clean up the city 
because they're junky looking." 
</P>
<P>
 The dumpster will be at 312 E. Commonwealth Ave. until Nov. 22. 
</P>
<P>
 Meacham said only campaign signs should be thrown in the dumpster. He said 
other trash will not be accepted. MIMI KO 
