<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; COUNCIL TO CONSIDER CHANGES IN MEETINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trying to make themselves more user-friendly, Ventura City Council members 
will consider Monday beginning their weekly meetings earlier and hearing public 
comments at the beginning of the meeting at least once a month. 
</P>
<P>
 Council meetings now start at 7:30 p.m. every Monday.In a special workshop 
this fall, council members proposed beginning the meetings at 7 p.m. in the 
hope that the meetings would end earlier. Council meetings now often end 
between 10:30 p.m. and 12:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 At the same workshop, council members also suggested changing the time of 
public comments. Now the public can comment on matters on the council's printed 
agenda as the issues are discussed. But comments about other topics cannot be 
made until the end of the meetings. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the new rules, on the first Monday of each month the council would take 
public comment at the beginning of its meeting. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
