<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WEST HILLS; JEWISH GROUPS PLAN HANUKKAH FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A candle-lighting ceremony, a children's play and contemporary and traditional 
Jewish music will be among the highlights of the West Valley Hanukkah Festival 
on Dec. 4. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled for the last day of Hanukkah, the festival will be the first of its 
kind sponsored by the West Valley Community Center, the San Fernando Valley 
Alliance Jewish Federation Council and three local temples. 
</P>
<P>
 Craig Taubman, a singer-songwriter known for his American-style Jewish music, 
will be the featured performer at the free festival, which will be held at 
Temple Aliyah in West Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to Taubman, a choir of canters will perform Hanukkah songs, 
according to Selma Sladek, spokeswoman for the West Valley Jewish Community 
Center. For teen-agers, the festival will host a workshop in tikkun olam , the 
Judaic concept of healing the world. 
</P>
<P>
 "The project will be making hats and caps for children who have undergone 
chemotherapy for cancer," Sladek said. "The decorated hats will be donated to 
these children." The festival is scheduled for noon to 5 p.m. For more 
information, call (818) 587-3300. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
