</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Juan Historical Society today will commemorate the renovation of a 
house that was under threat of the wrecking ball a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hankey/Rowse cottage, at 28232 Ortega Highway, was built around 1883, 
according to historical society members. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, the City Council did not want the house razed as part of a proposal 
for a housing subdivision because the cottage is on the city's list of historic 
and cultural landmarks. 
</P>
<P>
 A local contractor and his wife bought the cottage and one of the subdivision 
lots, where they relocated the structure and renovated it. 
</P>
<P>
 During a noon ceremony, a bronze plaque will be installed at the house. The 
public is invited. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 493-8444. JEFF BEAN 
