<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RELIGION IN SCHOOL? The question, "Does Religion Have Any Place in the Public 
Schools?" will be addressed by panelists Thursday night in Northridge at 
another in a series of public forums sponsored by the San Fernando Valley 
Interfaith Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Speakers will include Rabbi Jerald Brown of Temple Ahavat Shalom, Northridge; 
Joanne Zgonc of West Hills, a Roman Catholic; Pastor Ken Puccio of Holy 
Shepherd Lutheran Church, Chatsworth, and Patty Meade, a faculty member at 
Church on the Way's The King's Institute in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 The series moderator, the Rev. Jeff Utter of the Congregation Church of 
Chatsworth, will begin the program at 7:30 p.m. at the Northridge Seventh-day 
Adventist Church, 17700 Plummer St. The event, which is free, includes 
questions and discussion by participants. For information, call (818) 343-1205. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL DEDICATION: Formal dedication of a new campus on Mulholland Drive for 
the nation's only Reform Jewish high school will be held at 10 a.m. Sunday, led 
by Rabbi Isaiah Zeldin of Stephen S. Wise Temple. 
</P>
<P>
 The Stephen Wise Community Middle/High School, which has been located at the 
temple for its first two years, is moving most classes to temporary quarters on 
Mulholland just west of the San Diego Freeway. Work on permanent buildings has 
begun. 
</P>
<P>
 HOMELESS BENEFIT: There will be a concert of piano music by Chopin on Sunday 
night to benefit a cold weather program for the homeless in Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Pianist Judith Sandoval-Ferg will perform in the 7 p.m. event at 1211 N. Brand 
Blvd. Admission is free but an offering will be taken to support the Cold 
Weather Shelter Program sponsored by seven Glendale area churches and the 
Glendale Rotary Club. The National Guard Armory in Glendale will be used as a 
shelter mid-December through March. 
</P>
<P>
 JEWISH SONGS: A festival of Jewish songs will be held at 7:30 p.m. Tuesday at 
Valley Beth Shalom in Encino with performances by more than a dozen individuals 
and groups including Cantor Uri Frenkel, the Kol Echad Chorale, Sam and Judy 
Glass, Rabbi Joe Black and Kenny Ellis. 
</P>
<P>
 General admission is $12, reserved seating $18. For information, call (818) 
788-6000. 
</P>
<P>
 ADVENTIST SINGLES: A three-day seminar on sex and the single life, led by 
author Nancy Van Pelt, will begin at 7 p.m. Friday at the Northridge 
Seventh-day Adventist Church, 17700 Plummer St. A $40 registration fee for 
materials is payable at the door. 
</P>
<P>
 HAYFORD MOM: Dolores Hayford, an active family counselor and mother of Pastor 
Jack Hayford of Church on the Way, will speak Friday at the 8:30 a.m. breakfast 
meeting of Westlake Women's Aglow at the Canyon Club, 28912 Roadside Drive, 
Agoura Hills. Call (818) 597-9266 for reservations. JOHN DART 
</P>
