<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; MATER DEI KEEPS TWO STREAKS ALIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There were few surprises Friday night as undefeated Mater Dei beat winless 
Dana Hills, 42-13, in South Coast League action at Dana Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Monarch quarterback John Flynn was near-perfect in a little more than two 
quarters of play, throwing for four touchdowns and completing 11 of 12 passes 
for 256 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Flynn's main target was sophomore wide receiver Rod Perry, who caught three 
touchdown passes -- of 50, 57 and 17 yards -- and finished the night with eight 
receptions for 236 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The No. 2 Monarchs (10-0, 5-0) scored on every possession in the first half 
and on their opening drive of the second half before Coach Bruce Rollinson put 
in the reserves. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dolphins (0-10, 0-5) were able to hold Mater Dei scoreless for the 
remainder of the game, with the Monarchs' only first down coming on a 53-yard 
run by reserve running back Zachariah Pricer. Pricer took the ball to the 
Dolphins' four-yard line, where the defense kept them out of the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 The first of the Dolphins' two scoring plays came on a five-yard run by Jon 
Trottier early in the fourth quarter. After senior Matt Peters recovered an 
on-sides kick, Dana Hills moved the ball 53 yards on six plays and Scott 
Maynard connected with senior running back Robert Lathan on a 19-yard touchdown 
pass. 
</P>
<P>
 The Monarchs also got two touchdowns from senior Steve Bodnar, who finished 
the night with seven carries for 112 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
