<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; LOS AMIGOS FLIPS PACIFICA'S PLAYOFF 
HOPES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AHMED V. ORTIZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Amigos used a balanced attack to stymie Pacifica's playoff aspirations 
with a 35-19 Garden Grove League victory Friday night at Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
 A victory would have secured the league's third playoff spot for the Mariners 
(5-5-, 3-3), who are now at the mercy of the result of a coin flip with 
Santiago and Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 Eighth-ranked Los Amigos (9-1, 5-1) has already secured the league's second 
playoff spot. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lobos struck first with 3 minutes 7 seconds left in the first quarter on 
Greg Fausto's two-yard run. Each team committed two first-half turnovers, and 
although Pacifica's lone score of the half was set up by a fumble on a botched 
reverse, it was the Mariners who made the costlier mistakes. 
</P>
<P>
 After Ryan Johansen passed to Casey Huffmire for a 23-yard score, the Mariners 
lost track of Lobo fullback Niu Satele. On a third-and-six play on the ensuing 
possession, Neval Tuato spotted Satele alone at the 25. The 6-foot, 230-pounder 
then barreled over two tacklers to complete the 39-yard scoring play, giving 
the Lobos a 21-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 On the Lobos' next drive, Tuato connected with Satele on a similar play, this 
one covering 51 yards for a 28-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Satele finished with five catches for 120 yards. AHMED V. ORTIZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
