PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; BEDARD POWERS SERVITE PAST SANTA ANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Bedard scored five touchdowns and gained 140 total yards as Servite 
routed Santa Ana, 40-0, in a Golden West League game Friday night at Santa Ana 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Bedard accumulated 139 of his yards and four of his touchdowns in the first 
half.He also had a 35-yard touchdown run in the first half erased by a holding 
penalty. 
</P>
<P>
 After starting the opening drive on its 36 (its worst field position of the 
night), Servite (8-2, 5-0) started on Santa Ana's side of the field seven of 
their remaining nine possessions. The Saints' (1-9, 1-4) never started a drive 
on Servite's side of the field. Servite also turned Santa Ana turnovers into 21 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 Bedard started early, scoring on a 58-yard touchdown run on the game's second 
play to give the Friars a 6-0 lead.  
</P>
<P>
 After the Saints failed on a fourth-down opportunity, Bedard scored on an 
11-yard run three plays later. The two-point conversion failed and the Friars 
led, 12-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Bedard then scored from three yards out with 9 minutes 58 seconds left in the 
first half to give Servite a 19-0 lead. A 31-yard pass from David Martin to 
Bedard made it 26-0. Bedard had more total yards in the first half than Santa 
Ana (139-138). 
</P>
<P>
 Bedard carried the ball only once in the second half, and that produced a 
one-yard touchdown run to make it 33-0. TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
