<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; WHITTIER CHRISTIAN FALLS TO ONTARIO 
CHRISTIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Goudy rushed for 194 yards and a touchdown as Ontario Christian beat 
Whittier Christian, 30-8, in an Olympic League game Friday at Ontario Christian 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 With the victory, Ontario Christian (8-2, 3-2 in league) clinches a playoff 
spot.Whittier Christian (5-5, 1-4) ) lost five of its final six games. 
</P>
<P>
 Ontario Christian kept the ball on the ground for 36 of 37 plays from 
scrimmage. The only pass the Knights' Ben Goedhart attempted went for a 
touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 He and wide receiver Paul Voortman combined on a 73-yard touchdown pass to cap 
the scoring with 7 minutes 20 seconds left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Brett Kennon scored on runs of 16 and 15 yards in the first quarter for 
Ontario Christian. He finished with 102 yards in 13 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian cut into the lead when Jason McCleary scored on a 
three-yard run with 8:48 left in the first half. McCleary then ran in the 
two-point conversion, cutting the lead to 14-8. 
</P>
<P>
 But Ontario Christian came back to up the lead to 17-8 when Goedhart kicked a 
24-yard field goal with 2:29 left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Ontario Christian quickly added to the lead in the second half. Goudy ran 80 
yards for a touchdown on the first play from scrimmage. 
</P>
<P>
 Ontario Christian finished with 417 yards in total offense including 344 on 
the ground. Whittier Christian had 157 in total offense, all rushing. DALE RUHE 
</P>
