<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; OLYMPIC LEAGUE; KRUSE LIFTS CALVARY 
CHAPEL OVER BRETHREN CHRISTIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A touchdown run and two touchdown passes by Waylan Kruse helped Calvary Chapel 
past Brethren Christian, 34-15, Friday night at Artesia High. By winning, the 
Eagles finish in a tie for third and gained a probable playoff spot as a wild 
card. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors (1-9, 0-5) took the early lead when Ryan Babcock scored on a 
three-yard dive on the first possession of the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles did not waste time on their next drive (11 plays), which featured 
running back David Kuhn, who carried nine times for 61 yards. An eight-yard 
touchdown reception by Josh Young from Kruse tied the score, 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
 After the Warriors failed to convert on an Eagle fumble, Calvary Chapel took 
the lead on an 56-yard touchdown pass to Joe Jones from Kruse with 2:04 left in 
the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles (6-4, 3-2) buried Brethren Christian with two third-quarter 
touchdowns. Kruse scored the first on a two-yard run with 9:28 left in the 
third quarter. Eight minutes later, Kuhn, who finished the game with 89 yards 
rushing, scored on a three-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 An interception by Calvary Chapel's Eric Thulander set up three rushes by Ken 
Nash, the last a one-yard touchdown run, to make it 34-7 with 4:01 left to 
play. 
</P>
<P>
 Babcock, who completed 10 of 32 passes for 210 yards, rushed six yards for a 
touchdown with a minute left. JASON HILL 
</P>
