<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP WATER POLO PLAYOFFS; LA HABRA DOMINATES SADDLEBACK IN DIVISION II 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Habra's Dan Ploog made sure Saddleback's first playoff appearance in 14 
years didn't last long. He scored six first-half goals, leading La Habra to a 
13-8 victory over Saddleback in a Division II water polo playoff game Friday at 
La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra, seeded fourth, advances to play Tustin in a second-round game 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ploog scored three goals in a 3-minute, 7-second span of the first quarter, 
helping La Habra take a 4-2 lead. He scored his sixth goal on a penalty shot 
with 49 seconds left in the second quarter, and Brian Karol added a goal with 
10 seconds left, giving the Highlanders (20-6) an 8-3 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite the victory, La Habra Coach Jeff Hopkins said his team didn't play 
very well. 
</P>
<P>
 "It wasn't one of our better performances," Hopkins said. "We pressed on 
offense too much. But the guys played hard. Even in a game like that, where we 
didn't adapt to the referees, we still got the job done. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was an ugly game, but I'd rather have an ugly game this game than in the 
next round." 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra maintained its five-goal lead in the third quarter, and took a 12-5 
lead on a fast-break goal by Ploog with 2:49 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Hopkins then put his second-string players in the game, and Saddleback staged 
a quick three-goal rally to pull within 12-8 with 1:41 left. Hopkins then 
re-inserted his first string, and Karol capped the scoring on a goal with 40 
seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback (16-8) was led by Bret Trezise, who had four goals. GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</TEXT>
