<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP ALBUM CHART; NIRVANA, ONE MORE TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kurt Cobain mystique is in full bloom. Mourning fans, eager for a final 
musical memento of the late Nirvana leader, will make the group's "MTV 
Unplugged in New York," which entered the pop album chart at No. 1, one of the 
biggest year-end hits.Two albums gearing up to dominate the Christmas-music 
market just entered the chart--Mariah Carey's "Christmas" (No. 30) and Kenny 
G's "Miracles: The Holiday Album" (No. 38). Look for both to be in the Top 10 
by next month. Fans haven't taken to the rapping Digable Planets' new "Blowout 
Comb," which is plummeting down the chart--No. 71 and sinking. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Black Crowes are back with a new, classic-rock-styled album, "Amorica," 
which jumped on the chart at No. 11. The hoopla about the Stones' tour helps 
the Crowes. More fans are thinking about '60s and '70s rock these days. 
